<subSubSection id="C32E54C81601FFEEB59EE3966833CC4D" pageId="23" pageNumber="339" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8B07431601FFEEB59EE3966833CC4D" blockId="23.[160,1155,140,305]" pageId="23" pageNumber="339">
<emphasis id="B940DB511601FFEEB59EE3966BB4CDB5" box="[160,237,177,201]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="339">Worker</emphasis>
. Small species (TL 1.20–1.30). Head distinctly longer than broad, feebly convex or parallel sides and feebly concave posterior margin; eyes small with four or five ommatidia in the longest row; petiole peduncle in profile short and without anteroventral process. Body smooth and shining. Colour uniform yellow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
